title: Replies to initial written questions raised by Finance Committee Members in examining the Estimates of Expenditure 2010-11
question_text: With reference to the efforts to identify government properties with commercialisation potential, please give an account of what have been done and achieved by the Agency in this regard in the past three years, including the number and names of the government properties already identified as having such potential and those being processed.
reply_text: During 2007 to 2009, 76 government premises have been identified as having new commercialisation opportunities. Of these, seven have been leased through tendering; four have been/will be operated as government canteens; no positive response was received in relation to tender exercises/expression of interest exercises conducted in respect of 12 cases; tendering exercises in respect of seven cases are in progress and detailed studies are being conducted for nine cases. As for the remaining 37 cases, it was found not feasible to proceed with commercialisation after detailed analysis. In this regard, as government premises are primarily used as government offices or for the provision of public services and are not designed for commercial purposes, it is not unusual that commercialisation proposals cannot be pursued due to technical or other reasons after detailed study. A full list of these 76 governmentpremises is annexed.
